A Packet is a small segment of data transmitted over a network. It is the basic unit of data transmitted over a network. It is the basic unit of data transmission in a network and is used to 
transmit data between devices.
           STRUCTURE OF A PACKET
A packet consists of two main parts:
HEADER: The header contains control information, such source and source and destination IP addresses, port numbers, and packet sequence numbers.
PAYLOAD: The payload contains the actual data transmitted.
TYPES OF PACKETS
There are several types of packets, including:
DATA PACKETS: These packets contain actual data being transmitted.
ACKNOWLEDGMENT PACKETS (ACKs): These packets acknowledge receipt of data packets.
ERROR PACKETS: These packets indicate errors in transmission.
CONTROL PACKETS: These packets control the flow of data, such as packet sequence numbers.
